name: Jace, Architect of Thought
oracle_text: +1: Until your next turn, whenever a creature an opponent controls attacks, it gets -1/-0 until end of turn.
−2: Reveal the top three cards of your library. An opponent separates those cards into two piles. Put one pile into your hand and the other on the bottom of your library in any order.
−8: For each player, search that player's library for a nonland card and exile it, then that player shuffles their library. You may cast those cards without paying their mana costs.

name: Chronomaton
oracle_text: {1}, {T}: Put a +1/+1 counter on Chronomaton.
flavor_text: On the third night, the villagers destroyed their clocks. The sounds of whirring gears and chiming metal held only dread for them.

name: Jace's Phantasm
oracle_text: Flying
Jace's Phantasm gets +4/+4 as long as an opponent has ten or more cards in their graveyard.
flavor_text: In the abstract memories of the Iquati, Jace found interesting ideas to improve upon.

name: Phantasmal Bear
oracle_text: When Phantasmal Bear becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it.
flavor_text:
"You know it to be false, but when its claws find you, what you know won't matter much at all."
—Pol Jamaar, illusionist

name: Aether Figment
oracle_text: Kicker {3} (You may pay an additional {3} as you cast this spell.)
Aether Figment can't be blocked.
If Aether Figment was kicked, it enters the battlefield with two +1/+1 counters on it.

name: Crosstown Courier
oracle_text: Whenever Crosstown Courier deals combat damage to a player, that player puts that many cards from the top of their library into their graveyard.
flavor_text: Information travels quickly through Ravnica's network of messengers and thought agents.

name: Dream Stalker
oracle_text: When Dream Stalker enters the battlefield, return a permanent you control to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: What happens when it is the dream that wakes and the sleeper that fades into memory?

name: Krovikan Mist
oracle_text: Flying
Krovikan Mist's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Illusions on the battlefield.
flavor_text:
"It's as strong as you believe it is, and it's very convincing."
—Jace Beleren

name: Merfolk Wayfinder
oracle_text: Flying

When Merfolk Wayfinder enters the battlefield, reveal the top three cards of your library. Put all Island cards revealed this way into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Sea Gate Oracle
oracle_text: When Sea Gate Oracle enters the battlefield, look at the top two cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the other on the bottom of your library.
flavor_text: "The secret entrance should be near."

name: Stealer of Secrets
oracle_text: Whenever Stealer of Secrets deals combat damage to a player, draw a card.
flavor_text: The Dimir would hire her, if only they knew where she lived. The Azorius would condemn her, if only they knew her name.

name: Aether Adept
oracle_text: When Aether Adept enters the battlefield, return target creature to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: "The universe is my instrument, and the song I play upon it is one you are forbidden to hear."

name: Archaeomancer
oracle_text: When Archaeomancer enters the battlefield, return target instant or sorcery card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor_text: "Words of power never disappear. They sleep, awaiting those with the will to rouse them."

name: Phantasmal Dragon
oracle_text: Flying
When Phantasmal Dragon becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it.
flavor_text: Its hunger and ire are no less for being wrought of lies and mist.

name: Body Double
oracle_text: You may have Body Double enter the battlefield as a copy of any creature card in a graveyard.
flavor_text: "I am who I pretend to be."

name: Leyline Phantom
oracle_text: When Leyline Phantom deals combat damage, return it to its owner's hand. (Return it only if it survived combat.)
flavor_text:
"Is the maze itself a phantom? Or is one as real as the other? Perhaps I am as mad as the dragon."
—Jace Beleren, journal

name: Aeon Chronicler
oracle_text: Aeon Chronicler's power and toughness are each equal to the number of cards in your hand.

Whenever a time counter is removed from Aeon Chronicler while it's exiled, draw a card.

oracle_text: Flying

name: Errant Ephemeron
oracle_text: Flying

name: Thought Scour
oracle_text: Target player puts the top two cards of their library into their graveyard.
Draw a card.
flavor_text:
"As you inject the viscus vitae into the brain stem, don't let the spastic moaning bother you. It will soon become music to your ears."
—Stitcher Geralf

name: Agoraphobia
oracle_text: Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets -5/-0.
{2}{U}: Return Agoraphobia to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: "Everyone in this city is choosing sides. I choose inside."

name: Into the Roil
oracle_text: Kicker {1}{U} (You may pay an additional {1}{U} as you cast this spell.)
Return target nonland permanent to its owner's hand. If this spell was kicked, draw a card.
flavor_text: "Roil tide! Roil tide! Tie yourselves down!"

name: Memory Lapse
oracle_text: Counter target spell. If that spell is countered this way, put it on top of its owner's library instead of into that player's graveyard.
flavor_text:
"To sculpt a mind is to see every memory and thought as an individual piece that can be rearranged—or removed."
—Jace Beleren

oracle_text: Counter target spell. If that spell is countered this way, put it into its owner's hand instead of into that player's graveyard.
Draw a card.
flavor_text: For the Azorius, the law can be a physical shield against chaos and anarchy.

oracle_text: Enchant creature
When Claustrophobia enters the battlefield, tap enchanted creature.
Enchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.
flavor_text: Six feet of earth muffled his cries.

name: Griptide
oracle_text: Put target creature on top of its owner's library.
flavor_text:
"Beware the seagrafs just off the shore. These waters are filled with hungry geists looking for an easy meal."
—Captain Eberhart

name: Ray of Command
oracle_text: Untap target creature an opponent controls and gain control of it until end of turn. That creature gains haste until end of turn. When you lose control of the creature, tap it.
flavor_text: "Heel."

name: Control Magic
oracle_text: Enchant creature
You control enchanted creature.
flavor_text:
"Do as I think, not as I do."
—Jace Beleren

name: Summoner's Bane
oracle_text: Counter target creature spell. Create a 2/2 blue Illusion creature token.
flavor_text:
"I don't need to have the perfect plan. My foe just has to have an imperfect one."
—Jace Beleren

name: Jace's Ingenuity
oracle_text: Draw three cards.
flavor_text: "Brute force can sometimes kick down a locked door, but knowledge is a skeleton key."

name: Future Sight
oracle_text: Play with the top card of your library revealed.
You may play the top card of your library.
flavor_text:
"Is the inevitable any less miraculous?"
—Veldka, wandering sage

name: Spelltwine
oracle_text: Exile target instant or sorcery card from your graveyard and target instant or sorcery card from an opponent's graveyard. Copy those cards. Cast the copies if able without paying their mana costs. Exile Spelltwine.

When Halimar Depths enters the battlefield, look at the top three cards of your library, then put them back in any order.
{T}: Add {U}.

−3: Destroy target nonland permanent.
−7: Create three 1/1 black Assassin creature tokens with "Whenever this creature deals combat damage to a player, that player loses the game."

name: Pulse Tracker
oracle_text: Whenever Pulse Tracker attacks, each opponent loses 1 life.
flavor_text:
"You can't think your way out of this, Jace. Thought implies life, and life requires a pulse—music to a hunter's ears."
—Vraska

name: Shadow Alley Denizen
oracle_text: Whenever another black creature enters the battlefield under your control, target creature gains intimidate until end of turn. (It can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or creatures that share a color with it.)

name: Death-Hood Cobra

{1}{G}: Death-Hood Cobra gains deathtouch until end of turn.

name: Gatecreeper Vine

name: River Boa
oracle_text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)
{G}: Regenerate River Boa.
flavor_text:
"Sheath your swords! Cudgels only. I see a new pair of waterproof trek boots slithering away."
—Nablus, North Hada trapper

name: Vinelasher Kudzu

oracle_text: Pay 2 life: Putrid Leech gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Activate this ability only once each turn.
flavor_text:
"The Golgari would say that life comes from death and death comes from life. But sometimes, death comes from the dead."
—Vraska

name: Sadistic Augermage
oracle_text: When Sadistic Augermage dies, each player puts a card from their hand on top of their library.
flavor_text: "Don't worry. I know the drill."

name: Slate Street Ruffian
oracle_text: Whenever Slate Street Ruffian becomes blocked, defending player discards a card.

Whenever Spawnwrithe deals combat damage to a player, create a token that's a copy of Spawnwrithe.

oracle_text: {2}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Target opponent reveals their hand. You choose a card from it. That player discards that card. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery.
flavor_text: Those without breath can't complain.

flavor_text:
"Bury your dead deep. The boars are hungriest while the corpse is still warm."
—Paulin, trapper of Somberwald

name: Mold Shambler
oracle_text: Kicker {1}{G} (You may pay an additional {1}{G} as you cast this spell.)

name: Nekrataal

"You can't protect them all, Jace."
—Vraska

oracle_text: {2}{B}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Another target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor_text:

—Niszka, Selesnya evangel

oracle_text: Kicker {4} (You may pay an additional {4} as you cast this spell.)

flavor_text:

flavor_text: If you're looking for it, it's available. The question is how much you're willing to pay.

name: Consume Strength
oracle_text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Another target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor_text:
"You are correct. This is going to hurt."
—Vraska

oracle_text: Destroy target nonartifact creature. Its controller puts a number of cards equal to that creature's power from the top of their library into their graveyard.
flavor_text:

—Juri, proprietor of the Juri Revue

{T}: Add {B} or {G}.
flavor_text: Enter those who are starving and sick. You are welcome among the Swarm when the rest of Ravnica rejects you.

oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}.
{4}, {T}: Target creature can't be blocked this turn.
flavor_text: Rumors quickly spread among thieves about a labyrinth without walls and a prize beyond all measures of worth.
